One of the happiest exhibitions of his skill in language is in the piece first printed in the Knickerbocker Magazine, commencing—

Singing through the forests, Rattling over ridges,

Shooting under arches, Rumbling over bridges;

Whizzing through the mountains‚ Buzzing o'er the vale—

Bless me ! this is pleasant, Riding on a rail!

The whole composition is an echo and reflection of the crowded rail- road car. ·
